1. How to exchange data on Apple devices?
Firstly you need scan using your apple device to obtain the IOS version “One key Exchange”, then pair and connect according to the operation instructions, and start exchanging data after success.
"3. Why can't I switch Wi-Fi or turn off Wi-Fi hotspot during the exchange?"

"The data is transferred based on the principle of Wi-Fi hotspot and Wi-Fi channel is occupied, therefore you can't connect to the network through Wi-Fi. The data transfer will be interrupted if you switch Wi-Fi or turn off Wi-Fi hotspot."

Due to business needs, the app name had changed from “nubia File Transfer” to “One key Exchange” since V6.0.1 was released. Changing the app name will not affect the normal data transfer among different versions.
Please connect to the network and scan the QR code to download

You can also visit the application center or http://ui.nubia.cn/app download
2. Why is there a prompt that the old phone has insufficient backup space when data is selected?
The old phone requires about 500MB~1G space for data backup during the exchange.
Please do not change the network to avoid transmission interruption after exiting.
After exiting the hotspot, please do not change the network to avoid transmission interruption.
"5. Why can't some data be transferred successfully?"
Data transfer failure might be caused by any of the factors such as system version, app version, app’s compatibility or network problem.
After exiting, the application restoration will be suspended, the uninstalled apks are stored in Storage>flycow>apps

"7. Why can't WeChat Chat logs be transferred successfully?"

"If you have logged in WeChat, this might cause failure of transferring some chat logs during the exchange. It is recommended to exit WeChat before exchange. Due to Android feature, WeChat and other application data transmissions are not supported for Android 8.0 and above or non-nubia models."
6. Which data cannot be transferred via One Key Exchange?

System apps (Flashlight, Calculator, nubia Store, nubia Community, Email) cannot be transferred when exchanging from a Nubia phone to another nubia phone; App data cannot be transferred when exchanging from a non-Nubia phone to a Nubia phone.
4. What if disconnection occurs or connection terminates exceptionally during the exchange?

It will reconnected automatically after disconnection; if reconnection fails, scan to connect again; if you click the Back key to exit the app, you can resume transfer through history or scanning entry when you enter the app next time.
